/target
*.mind
*.mind-wal
# Python bindings build/test scaffolding (bindings/python): wheels land in
# target/wheels, the local venv and pytest/maturin caches are throwaway.
.venv/
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
fuzz/target
fuzz/artifacts
# The Python bindings are their own workspace with its own target/ (wheels land
# in bindings/python/target/wheels); the crate is excluded from the root
# workspace, so the root /target rule does not cover it.
bindings/python/target
# Materialized benchmark datasets are large build products regenerated from the
# committed specs (benches/src/dataset.rs), never committed themselves.
benches/data/
# Harness output. `latest.md` is a scratch render; per-version result JSONs are
# published only when a release is cut (docs/BENCHMARKS.md §4 rule 3) by
# force-adding the specific file — the dev-run noise stays out of the tree.
benches/results/
